('App\\Models\\Blog', 2, 'en', 'title', 'Baking 101: Tips for Perfect Pastries and Baked Goods'),
('App\\Models\\Blog', 2, 'en', 'description', 'Baking is both an art and a science—it requires precision and the right techniques. One of the most important factors is measuring ingredients accurately; even small deviations can affect the outcome. Having ingredients like eggs and butter at room temperature helps you achieve a smoother batter or dough. Preheating the oven is critical; placing batter into a cold oven often leads to uneven baking. Knowing your oven also matters—many ovens have hot spots, so rotating trays mid-bake can help achieve even results. Mixing methods such as folding, whisking, and beating influence the final texture. Beginners should start with simple recipes and build confidence before attempting advanced techniques. Finally, allow cakes and pastries to cool before frosting to prevent melting and a messy finish. With practice and patience, anyone can become a better baker.'),
('App\\Models\\Blog', 2, 'en', 'meta_title', 'Perfect Pastries and Baking Tips'),
('App\\Models\\Blog', 2, 'en', 'meta_description', 'Practical tips and techniques to improve your baking results.'),
